      "content": "it’s nice you say that, but there isn't really anyone left to reach out to. my kids are busy with their own lives and my friends are mostly gone now. and even if they were here, what would i say? 'help me, i'm old and everything hurts'? it's just a cycle of being a burden. it feels like i'm just occupying space while i wait for the inevitable. it would be so much more peaceful if i could just decide when it's over, instead of just letting it drag on like this.",
