      "content": "i know, i know... people always say that. but i don't want \"help\" to just manage the decline. there's no dignity in just waiting for my heart to stop or for a fall to do it for me. it feels like i've lost all my agency. wouldn't it be more dignified, more actually \"peaceful\" to just take charge of the situation? to have some control over the end instead of just being a passive victim to my own aging?",
